==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thickset
<hw>Thick"set`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Close
planted; <as>as, a <ex>thickset</ex> wood; a <ex>thickset</ex>
hedge</as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a short, thick body; stout.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thickset</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thickset
<hw>Thick"set`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A close or thick
hedge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A stout, twilled cotton cloth; a fustian corduroy,
or velveteen.</def> <rj><au>McElrath.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thickskin</ent>⟦br⟧
